                            <comment id="13292333" author="celestin" created="Sat, 9 Jun 2012 13:14:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug was revealed while working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-795&quot; title=&quot;Refactoring ArrayRealVectorTest, RealVectorTest, SparseRealVectorTest&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MATH-795&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MATH-795&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Previous unit tests didn&apos;t show that bug, because in &lt;tt&gt;RealVectorTest&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;TestVectorImpl&lt;/tt&gt; used to override the default implementation of &lt;tt&gt;RealVector.subtract(RealVector)&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is now corrected in &lt;tt&gt;r1348396&lt;/tt&gt; (tests to be updated following work on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-795&quot; title=&quot;Refactoring ArrayRealVectorTest, RealVectorTest, SparseRealVectorTest&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MATH-795&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MATH-795&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
